eepun%20(radicalised%20Meitei%20youths)%20and%20some%20women.%20For%20over%20half%20an%20hour%2C%20these%20men%20kicked%20us%20around%20like%20kids%20playing%20with%20a%20football.%20Groups%20of%20men%20were%20jumping%20on%20us%E2%80%A6.%20I%20am%20at%20a%20loss%20for%20words%20to%20describe%20what%20happened%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689938570000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30163218%2FFwqAt6VXsAIGp1_.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-video-tarnished-states-image-says-cm-biren-calls-for-statewide-protests%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Because%20this%20state%20that%20we%20have%2C%20the%20people%20who%20live%20in%20it%2C%20they%20consider%20women%20their%20mothers.%20But%20miscreants%20did%20this%20and%20tarnished%20our%20image%2C'%20said%20Biren.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-video-tarnished-states-image-says-cm-biren-calls-for-statewide-protests%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22DU%20Student%20Detained%20Without%20Orders%20Ahead%20of%20PM%20Event%20Files%20Police%20Complaint%20After%20HC%20Green%20Light%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30141622%2FUntitled-design-14.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Delhi%20University%20student%20activist%20Abhigyan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelhi-police-camps-inside-du-student-activists-house-bars-them-from-leaving-during-pm-event%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20confined%20to%20his%20house%20by%20Model%20Town%20constables%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20June%2030%20during%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20campus%20%E2%80%93%20has%20filed%20a%20formal%20complaint%20of%20wrongful%20confinement%20with%20his%20local%20police%20station%20after%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20said%20he%20had%20the%20right%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20green%20light%20came%20after%20counsel%20for%20the%20Delhi%20police%2C%20Sanjay%20Lao%2C%20told%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20court%20that%20there%20were%20no%20preventive%20detention%20orders%20against%20Abhighyan.%20The%20cour%3Cspan%3Et%20was%20hearing%20a%20writ%20petition%20by%20Abhigyan%20alleging%20that%20his%20preventive%20detention%20was%20illegal%20as%20it%20was%20without%20orders.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbhigyan%20had%20also%20petitioned%20the%20court%20to%20declare%20his%20confinement%20as%20illegal%20and%20issue%20a%20writ%20of%20mandamus%20censuring%20the%20practice%20of%20arbitrary%20detention.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20bench%20comprising%20Justices%20Siddharth%20Mridul%20and%20Gaurang%20Kanth%20said%20it%20would%20be%20premature%20for%20the%20court%20to%20issue%20such%20a%20declaration%2C%20it%20granted%20him%20liberty%20on%20July%2012%20to%20file%20a%20complaint%20with%20the%20Model%20Town%20police%E2%80%99s%20station%20house%20officer%20(SHO).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2017%2C%20Abhigyan%20filed%20a%20formal%20complaint%20with%20the%20Model%20Town%20SHO%20against%20constables%20Kaberi%20and%20Amit%20Kumar%20citing%20several%20sections%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20including%20those%20relating%20to%20wrongful%20confinement%20and%20criminal%20intimidation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20was%20duly%20received%20and%20the%20police%20will%20now%20have%20to%20conduct%20a%20preliminary%20investigation%20before%20registering%20%E2%80%93%20or%20refusing%20to%20register%20%E2%80%93%20an%20FIR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIllegal%20custody%20is%20an%20anathema%20and%20antithesis%20of%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20but%20the%20law%20applies%20equally%20to%20the%20police%20as%20it%20does%20to%20you%20%E2%80%A6%20Your%20allegation%20is%20for%20illegal%20detention.%20You%20file%20a%20complaint.%20The%20police%20%5Bdo%5D%20not%20have%20any%20immunity%20for%20their%20action%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Mridul%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fhigh-court%2Fdelhi-high-court%2Fdelhi-high-court-complaint-delhi-police-aisa-activist-illegal-detention-prime-minister-visit-du-232540%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eremarked%20orally%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20according%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20likened%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20court%20making%20such%20a%20declaration%20at%20that%20stage%20in%20the%20case%20to%20%E2%80%9Cputting%20the%20cart%20before%20the%20horse%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbhigyan%20is%20a%20student%20at%20Delhi%20University%20(DU)%20and%20president%20of%20the%20Delhi%20chapter%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Students%E2%80%99%20Association%20(AISA)%2C%20a%20student%20body%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20230701023648%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.aisa.in%2Fabout%2Fmanifesto%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eassociated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist-Leninist)%20Liberation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20was%20confined%20by%20police%20along%20with%20fellow%20DU%20student%20and%20AISA%20general%20secretary%20Anjali%20in%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20home%20on%20June%2030%2C%20hours%20ahead%20of%20a%20ceremony%20in%20the%20university%E2%80%99s%20centenary%20celebrations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30142414%2FIMG-20230630-WA0009-1-1024x576.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30142414%2FIMG-20230630-WA0009-1-1024x576.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30142414%2FIMG-20230630-WA0009-1-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30142414%2FIMG-20230630-WA0009-1.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-660936%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EConstables%20from%20the%20Model%20Town%20police%20station%20inside%20the%20student%20activist%E2%80%99s%20home.%20Photo%3A%20Special%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20was%20booked%20as%20the%20ceremony%E2%80%99s%20chief%20guest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20university%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdu-colleges-stir-controversy-with-mandatory-attendance-for-valedictory-ceremony%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewent%20out%20of%20its%20way%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20ensure%20student%20compliance%20during%20the%20ceremony%2C%20with%20some%20of%20its%20colleges%20mandating%20attendance%20at%20screenings%20of%20the%20event%20and%20barring%20students%20from%20wearing%20black-coloured%20clothing%2C%20a%20common%20symbol%20of%20dissent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModel%20Town%20police%20allegedly%20told%20Abhigyan%20and%20Anjali%20that%20they%20were%20being%20detained%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%9D%20as%20they%20%E2%80%9Cmight%20create%20%5Ba%5D%20ruckus%20at%20the%20DU%20event%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConstables%20Kaberi%20and%20Amit%20Kumar%20camped%20in%20Anjali%E2%80%99s%20home%20for%20five%20hours%20on%20June%2030%20starting%20at%20around%209%20am%20and%20allegedly%20threatened%20to%20arrest%20the%20AISA%20activists%20if%20they%20tried%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20also%20allegedly%20told%20Abhigyan%20that%20there%20were%20no%20orders%20for%20his%20and%20Anjali%E2%80%99s%20detention%2C%20something%20that%20has%20since%20been%20corroborated%20by%20standing%20counsel%20Lao%20in%20court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Shahrukh%20Alam%2C%20who%20represented%20Abhigyan%20in%20the%20high%20court%2C%20said%20that%20their%20case%20centred%20on%20the%20circumstances%20under%20which%20someone%E2%80%99s%20fundamental%20rights%20to%20personal%20liberty%20(Article%2021%20of%20the%20constitution)%20and%20protection%20from%20arbitrary%20detention%20(Article%2022)%20may%20be%20breached.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20two%20questions%20for%20consideration%20are%3A%20(1)%20If%20the%20breach%20of%20liberty%20is%20only%20for%20a%20few%20hours%2C%20is%20it%20acceptable%20to%20suspend%20%5Bsomeone%E2%80%99s%5D%20Article%2021%20and%20Article%2022%20rights%3F%20(2)%20If%20the%20breach%20of%20liberty%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Evis-a-vis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20known%20protestors%2C%20raucous%20student%20activists%20and%20dissenters%2C%20is%20it%20acceptable%20to%20suspend%20%5Btheir%5D%20Article%2021%20and%20Article%2022%20rights%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlam%20said%20the%20answer%20to%20these%20questions%20is%20to%20be%20found%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EK.S.%20Puttaswamy%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20in%20which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EADM%20Jabalpur%20v.%20Shivkant%20Shukla%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20judgement%20which%20had%20endorsed%20the%20suspension%20of%20fundamental%20rights%20during%20emergency%2C%20should%20be%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fthe-verdict-of-history-adm-jabalpur-case-5942547%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eburied%20ten%20fathoms%20deep%20and%20is%20never%20to%20be%20resurrected%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20the%20primacy%20of%20fundamental%20rights%20is%20well%20established%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20argued.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-chandrachud-judgment-right-to-privacy%5C%22%3EKey%20Highlights%20of%20Justice%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20Judgment%20in%20the%20Right%20to%20Privacy%20Case%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbhigyan%E2%80%99s%20lawyers%20also%20noted%20in%20their%20writ%20petition%20dated%20July%2010%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20held%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F564452%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edifferent%20case%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20under%20Article%2022%20(5)%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20authorities%20who%20order%20the%20preventive%20detention%20of%20a%20person%20must%20communicate%20the%20grounds%20of%20the%20order%20to%20that%20person%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20argued%20that%20as%20Abhigyan%20was%20never%20provided%20with%20an%20order%20(or%20grounds%20for%20an%20order)%20relating%20to%20his%20detention%2C%20his%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2022%20had%20been%20violated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlam%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20July%2012%20order%20granting%20liberty%20to%20Abhigyan%20was%20especially%20significant%20because%20of%20a%20letter%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20registrar%20general%20sent%20to%20the%20Model%20Town%20SHO%20asking%20for%20their%20immediate%20compliance%20with%20the%20order.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20significant%20for%20the%20cover%20letter%20from%20the%20registrar%20general%20to%20the%20SHO%20of%20the%20Model%20Town%20police%20station%20directing%20immediate%20compliance%20with%20the%20order.%20It%20is%20interesting%20because%20normally%2C%20orders%20aren%E2%80%99t%20directly%20communicated%20to%20police%20stations%2C%20unless%20it%20is%20a%20habeas%20corpus%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20habeas%20corpus%20cases%2C%20when%20someone%20is%20under%20illegal%20detention%2C%20orders%20are%20sent%20to%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20custodian.%20But%20Abhigyan%E2%80%99s%20is%20not%20a%20habeas%20corpus%20case%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20a%20preventive%20detention%20case%2C%20and%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Epost%20facto%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%5Bafter%20the%20fact%5D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20action%20recognises%20that%20Abhigyan%E2%80%99s%20detention%20was%20illegal%20as%20there%20were%20no%20orders%20for%20it%2C%20and%20that%20cases%20like%20these%20are%20becoming%20a%20pattern%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21135811%2FAnjali-and-Abhigyan-1024x768.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22627%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21135811%2FAnjali-and-Abhigyan-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21135811%2FAnjali-and-Abhigyan-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%