Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20the%20incident%20put%20her%20and%20Abhigyan%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20evicted%20from%20her%20rented%20flat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EManik%20Gupta%2C%20the%20AISA%E2%80%99s%20Delhi%20University%20president%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20police%20excesses%20in%20relation%20to%20DU%20students%20is%20not%20a%20new%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CStudents%20are%20detained%20without%20any%20reasoning%20for%20holding%20peaceful%20protests%2C%20false%20FIRs%20are%20filed%20to%20intimidate%20activists%20and%20excessive%20use%20of%20physical%20force%20has%20become%20a%20norm%20to%20crush%20dissent%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20alleged.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689937213000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Faisa-activist-abhigyan-granted-liberty-to-file-complaint%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22All%20India%20Students%20Association%20activists%20Abhigyan%20and%20Anjali%20were%20allegedly%20illegally%20confined%20by%20the%20Delhi%20police%20on%20June%2030%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%9D%20as%20they%20%E2%80%9Cmight%20create%20%5Ba%5D%20ruckus%20at%20the%20DU%20event%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Everybody%20Now%20Is%20Touchy%20About%20Everything'%3A%20SC%20Rejects%20PIL%20To%20Revoke%20CBFC%20Clearance%20to%20'Adipirush'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F21153609%2FAdipurush-OTT-Release-Date-2023.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%2C%20July%2021%2C%20dismissed%20a%20petition%20seeking%20the%20cancellation%20of%20the%20censor%20certificate%20granted%20to%20%3Cem%3EAdipurush%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20observing%20that%20the%20court%20cannot%20interfere%20with%20film%20certifications%20based%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Csensitivities%20of%20each%20individual%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20%E2%80%93%20based%20on%20the%20Ramayana%20%E2%80%93%20has%20received%20a%20cold%20reception%20from%20critics%20and%20fans%20alike%2C%20with%20many%20protesting%20against%20its%20dialogues%20and%20for%20deviating%20from%20the%20mythology.%20Petitions%20have%20been%20filed%20against%20it%20in%20several%20high%20courts%2C%20with%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20slamming%20the%20makers%20of%20the%20movie%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fadipurush-hindu-dialogue-allahabad-high-court%5C%22%3Etesting%20the%20tolerance%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20of%20Hindus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20S.K.%20Kaul%20and%20Sudhanshu%20Dhulia%20on%20Friday%20dismissed%20the%20public%20interest%20litigation%20(PIL)%20filed%20by%20advocate%20Mamta%20Rani%2C%20saying%20that%20%3Cem%3EAdipurush%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20portrayal%20of%20Hindu%20deities%20%E2%80%9Cviolated%20the%20statutory%20provisions%20outlined%20in%20Section%205B%20of%20the%20Cinematograph%20Act%2C%201952%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-dismisses-plea-against-adipurush-movie-233290%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Justice%20Kaul%20expressed%20concerns%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9Cincreasing%20trend%20of%20people%20bringing%20every%20minor%20issue%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20asking%20if%20the%20court%20should%20be%20scrutinising%20every%20aspect%20of%20films%2C%20books%2C%20and%20artworks%E2%80%9D.%20The%20judge%20%E2%80%93%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-justice-sk-kaul-obscenity-perumal-murugan%5C%22%3Edelivered%20landmark%20verdicts%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%2C%20upholding%20the%20rights%20of%20artists%20M.F.%20Husain%20and%20author%20Perumal%20Murugan%20%E2%80%93%20said%20there%20should%20be%20a%20certain%20level%20of%20tolerance%20towards%20creative%20representations.%20He%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20should%20we%20entertain%20this%20under%20%5BArticle%5D%2032%20%5Bwhich%20gives%20citizens%20the%20right%20to%20seek%20constitutional%20remedy%20from%20the%20Supreme%20Court%5D%3F%20The%20Cinematography%20Act%20provides%20for%20the%20method%20to%20get%20%5Ba%5D%20certificate.%20Everybody%20now%20is%20touchy%20about%20everything.%20Every%20time%20they%20will%20come%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20it.%20Is%20everything%20to%20be%20scrutinised%20by%20us%3F%20The%20level%20of%20tolerance%20for%20films%2C%20books%2C%20paintings%20keeps%20on%20getting%20down.%20Now%20people%20are%20hurt%20maybe%20sometimes%20genuinely%2C%20maybe%20sometimes%20not.%20But%20we%20will%20not%20under%20Article%2032%20start%20entertaining%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20petitioner%20argued%20that%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Film%20Certification%20(CBFC)%20did%20not%20adhere%20to%20the%20required%20guidelines%20before%20granting%20the%20clearance%2C%20the%20bench%20was%20reluctant%20to%20entertain%20the%20PIL%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20order%2C%20Justice%20Kaul%20said%20that%20cinematographic%20representations%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20not%20be%20an%20exact%20replica%20of%20religious%20texts%20and%20that%20artistic%20freedom%20must%20be%20balanced%20with%20limits%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20may%20say%20this%20at%20the%20inception%20itself%20that%20cinematographic%20representations%20may%20not%20be%20the%20exact%20replica%20of%20text.%20There%20has%20to%20be%20a%20certain%20play.%20However%2C%20so%20that%20the%20play%20does%20not%20go%20beyond%20a%20certain%20limit%2C%20a%20body%20has%20been%20constituted%20to%20look%20into%20these%20aspects.%20In%20the%20present%20case%2C%20the%20certificate%20was%20issued%20by%20that%20body%20and%20there%20has%20been%20certain%20modifications%20made%20after%20that%20too.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20interferes%20based%20on%20the%20sensitivities%20of%20each%20person%2C%20it%20would%20not%20%E2%80%9Cbecome%20some%20kind%20of%20an%20appellate%20authority%20for%20the%20censor%20board.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fadipurush-is-probably-the-most-tacky-derivative-and-unnecessary-film-of-the-year%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Adipurush%E2%80%99%20Is%20Probably%20the%20Most%20Tacky%2C%20Derivative%20and%20Unnecessary%20Film%20of%20the%20Year%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECourt%20grants%20interim%20relief%20to%20makers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20matter%2C%20the%20top%20court%20also%20granted%20interim%20relief%20to%20the%20makers%20of%20%3Cem%3EAdipurush%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%20stayed%20the%20proceedings%20against%20the%20film%20in%20various%20high%20courts%20and%20issued%20notice%20on%20a%20transfer%20petition%20and%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20producer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-adipurush-movie-stays-proceedings-in-high-courts-against-makers-of-233281%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20petition%20filed%20before%20the%20Allahabad%20HC%20sought%20a%20ban%20on%20the%20movie%20for%20%E2%80%9Churting%20the%20sentiments%20of%20Hindus%E2%80%9D%20by%20%E2%80%9Cdestroying%20their%20fundamental%20values%20and%20characters%E2%80%9D%20and%20modifying%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbasic%20structure%E2%80%9D%20of%20Valmiki%20Ramayana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20sought%20the%20personal%20presence%20of%20the%20movie%E2%80%99s%20director%20(Om%20Raut)%2C%20producer%