%2023%2C%20a%20Surat%20court%20had%20convicted%20Gandhi%20in%20a%20criminal%20defamation%20case%20based%20on%20a%20complaint%20filed%20by%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20leader%20and%20Gujarat%20minister%20Purnesh%20Modi%2C%20and%20sentenced%20him%20to%20two%20years%20of%20imprisonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20complaint%20had%20been%20filed%20after%20a%202019%20pre-election%20campaign%20speech%20by%20Gandhi%20at%20Kolar%20in%20Karnataka.%20In%20it%2C%20Gandhi%20had%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20a%20question.%20Why%20do%20all%20these%20thieves%20have%20Modi%20in%20their%20names%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20Nirav%20Modi%2C%20Lalit%20Modi%20or%20Narendra%20Modi%3F%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20many%20more%20such%20Modis%20will%20come%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPurnesh%20Modi%20had%20alleged%20this%20was%20defamatory%20to%20people%20with%20the%20%E2%80%98Modi%E2%80%99%20last%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Surat%20court%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Frahul-gandhi-to-challenge-conviction-in-defamation-case-today%5C%22%3Esuspended%3C%2Fa%3E%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20two-year%20sentence%20and%20granted%20bail%2C%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20had%2C%20on%20July%207%2C%20refused%20to%20stay%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20conviction%20and%20the%20two-year%20sentence%20given%20to%20him.%20A%20stay%20would%20have%20meant%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20reinstatement%20to%20parliament%20ahead%20of%20the%20Monsoon%20Session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Justices%20B.R.%20Gavai%20and%20Prashant%20Kumar%20Mishra%20today%20heard%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-congress-leader-rahul-gandhi-defamation-case-modi-remark-233264%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported%20that%20Justice%20Gavai%20sought%20to%20clarify%20that%20his%20father%20%E2%80%93%20former%20governor%20of%20three%20states%20and%20former%20MP%20of%20both%20houses%2C%20R.S.%20Gavai%20%E2%80%93%20had%20been%20associated%20with%20the%20Congress.%20Justice%20Gavai%20also%20added%20that%20his%20brother%2C%20Rajendra%20Gavai%2C%20is%20still%20associated%20with%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20asked%20if%20there%20was%20objection%20to%20him%20hearing%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20sides%2C%20represented%20by%20senior%20advocates%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%20and%20Mahesh%20Jethmalani%2C%20said%20they%20had%20none.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20said%20that%20the%20next%20hearing%20date%20would%20be%20August%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESinghvi%2C%20for%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20requested%20an%20earlier%20hearing%20date%2C%20considering%20that%20the%20Monsoon%20Session%20of%20the%20parliament%20would%20end%20on%20August%2011%20and%20the%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20could%20impact%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20attend%20the%20lower%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESinghvi%20highlighted%20that%20Gandhi%20has%20lost%20over%20a%20hundred%20days%20as%20an%20MP%2C%20including%20an%20entire%20session%20and%20part%20of%20the%20current%20session.%20Gandhi%20represents%20the%20Wayanad%20constituency%20in%20Kerala%2C%20where%20by-elections%20to%20fill%20his%20spot%20could%20be%20notified%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Jethmalani%20sought%2010%20days%20to%20file%20a%20reply.%20When%20Justice%20Gavai%20cited%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20had%20been%20over%20100%20pages%20and%20asked%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20is%20the%20need%20for%20reply%20in%20such%20a%20matter%3F%E2%80%9D%2C%20Jethmalani%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20put%20on%20record%20%E2%80%9Ccertain%20propositions%20of%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeculiar%20thing%20we%20are%20seeing%20from%20Gujarat%20HC%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Gavai%20additionally%20said%2C%20on%20the%20Gujarat%20HC%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Hemant%20Pra